column5: CLRB A number of brokerages have recently commented on CLRB Zacks Investment Research raised Cellectar Biosciences from a hold rating to a buy rating and set a 325 price objective for the company in a research report on Thursday May 16th HC Wainwright assumed coverage on Cellectar Biosciences in a report on Thursday May 2nd They issued a buy rating and a 400 target price on the stock Finally ValuEngine cut Cellectar Biosciences from a buy rating to a hold rating in a report on Wednesday May 1st
CLRB up about 12 is last three days

Although CLRB is quiet it is slowly but surely going up with no news whatsoever The minute a PR comes out hang on Yes I am a bagholder but I cant get rid of something that will pay off a few bills SOON Stop loss is in 210220 range PT is above 3 short term and 10 for the PAYtient ones
